description:
&lt;p&gt;Strategic Planning &amp; Performance: An exciting opportunity has arisen with this dynamic and fast-growing team. We are keen to hear from you if you are looking for the next step in your career in project management that will expose you to a variety of projects and hone your project management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Strategic Planning and Performance Team is is a busy, high-volume and friendly environment that will suit an organised person with a great eye for detail and plenty of team spirit. Reporting to the Head of Programme Management Office and working with other project team members, you will be adept at managing and overseeing multiple projects. You will already have experience in project management methodologies and technologies, perhaps from undertaking a structured learning opportunity or building your own knowledge, and are ready for your next personal development challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who can:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the organisation and planning of complex meetings, such as project boards and gateway review meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce Project Initiation Document (PID) for straightforward projects, working with Senior Managers, Partners and Stakeholders including:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scoping the project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shaping the project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying interdependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate and motivate teams on project delivery including linking in with other initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of working on projects, standard office procedures and an understanding of project/programme methodology and monitoring is essential for the role. Just as important is your personal commitment to delivering on your key objectives and providing a client-focused service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
